            </p:ValueBoxSettings>
          </Pad>
          <Pad Id="QCqLWyieVEJNyJZnOx7Yrt" Bounds="14,79,312,35" ShowValueBox="true" isIOBox="true" Value="Explanation RoutedEvents">
            <p:TypeAnnotation LastCategoryFullName="Primitive" LastDependency="VL.CoreLib.vl">
              <Choice Kind="TypeFlag" Name="String" />
            </p:TypeAnnotation>
            <p:ValueBoxSettings>
              <p:fontsize p:Type="Int32">16</p:fontsize>
              <p:stringtype p:Assembly="VL.Core" p:Type="VL.Core.StringType">Comment</p:stringtype>
            </p:ValueBoxSettings>
          </Pad>
          <Pad Id="RErUp1kqkdkPMlsnOYFbZK" Bounds="14,120,437,76" ShowValueBox="true" isIOBox="true" Value="There is a special category of events in Avalonia used for low-level interactions. Generally, developers should avoid these in favor of &quot;Commands&quot; and &quot;Properties&quot;. However, for low-level customizations and UI flow control, manual event handling is necessary.">
            <p:TypeAnnotation LastCategoryFullName="Primitive" LastDependency="VL.CoreLib.vl">
              <Choice Kind="TypeFlag" Name="String" />
            </p:TypeAnnotation>
            <p:ValueBoxSettings>
              <p:fontsize p:Type="Int32">9</p:fontsize>
              <p:stringtype p:Assembly="VL.Core" p:Type="VL.Core.StringType">Comment</p:stringtype>
            </p:ValueBoxSettings>
          </Pad>
          <Pad Id="KiNapHx5rpINNuhm0xr2Ax" Bounds="14,214,437,76" ShowValueBox="true" isIOBox="true" Value="A common example is using a `SkiaLayerControl` where you need to stop a `KeyPress` from bubbling to the focus navigation. Pressing the &quot;Up&quot; arrow key woud trigger a focus move rather then handled by control.">
            <p:TypeAnnotation LastCategoryFullName="Primitive" LastDependency="VL.CoreLib.vl">
              <Choice Kind="TypeFlag" Name="String" />
            </p:TypeAnnotation>
            <p:ValueBoxSettings>
              <p:fontsize p:Type="Int32">9</p:fontsize>
              <p:stringtype p:Assembly="VL.Core" p:Type="VL.Core.StringType">Comment</p:stringtype>
            </p:ValueBoxSettings>
          </Pad>
          <Pad Id="F95sTmtd8rMMoTkIedju9I" Bounds="14,310,666,65" ShowValueBox="true" isIOBox="true" Value="To handle these scenarios, the following nodes are available:&#xD;&#xA;* RoutedEventListener - A customizable node for general event handling.&#xD;&#xA;* Specialized Listeners - Pre-configured listeners for specific actions (e.g., `ClickRoutedEventListener`).">
            <p:TypeAnnotation LastCategoryFullName="Primitive" LastDependency="VL.CoreLib.vl">
              <Choice Kind="TypeFlag" Name="String" />
            </p:TypeAnnotation>
            <p:ValueBoxSettings>
              <p:fontsize p:Type="Int32">9</p:fontsize>
              <p:stringtype p:Assembly="VL.Core" p:Type="VL.Core.StringType">Comment</p:stringtype>
            </p:ValueBoxSettings>
          </Pad>
          <Pad Id="E0H1NJqGurTLexQipqOvDR" Bounds="14,412,783,67" ShowValueBox="true" isIOBox="true" Value="The `RoutedEventListener` comes in two variants depending on how you wish to target the event:&#xD;&#xA;1. `RoutedEventListener`- Provide the event as a direct reference.&#xD;&#xA;2. `RoutedEventListener (Name)` - Provide the event by its string name.">
            <p:TypeAnnotation LastCategoryFullName="Primitive" LastDependency="VL.CoreLib.vl">
              <Choice Kind="TypeFlag" Name="String" />
            </p:TypeAnnotation>
            <p:ValueBoxSettings>
              <p:fontsize p:Type="Int32">9</p:fontsize>
              <p:stringtype p:Assembly="VL.Core" p:Type="VL.Core.StringType">Comment</p:stringtype>
            </p:ValueBoxSettings>
          </Pad>
